1 → 2 → 3 → 2 → 1
true

Steps
  Find middle of linked list
  Reverse second half
  Compare first half and reversed second half
  If all equal → palindrome
🔹 Example

Linked List:1 → 2 → 3 → 2 → 1
Step 1: Find Middle
    Using slow & fast pointers: 
    slow moves 1 step
    fast moves 2 steps
    Middle: 3
Step 2: Reverse Second Half
  Original: 3 → 2 → 1
  Reverse:  1 → 2 → 3
Step 3: Compare
    Compare:
        1 == 1
        2 == 2
        3 == 3
    All equal ✅

/*
class Node {
    int data;
    Node next;

    Node(int d) {
        data = d;
        next = null;
    }
}*/

class Solution {
    public boolean isPalindrome(Node head) {
        
        if(head==null || head.next==null){
            return true;
        }
        // code here
        Node slow =head;
        Node fast = head;
        
        while (fast!=null && fast.next !=null){
            slow = slow.next;
            fast= fast.next.next;
        }
        Node temp =null;
        Node curr= slow;
        while (curr!=null){
            Node nextTemp= curr.next;
            curr.next=temp;
            
            temp=curr;
            curr=nextTemp;
        }
        
        Node first= head;
        Node second = temp;
       while (second!=null){
           if(first.data !=second.data){
               return false;
           }
           first= first.next;
           second=second.next;
       }
        return true;
    }
}
